---
title: Curried Sweet Potato Dosa-Dillas with Chickpeas, Mozzarella, Charred Corn Salsa & Yogurt
description: Go ahead and skip the takeout menu with these “dosa-dillas”—a mashup of Indian flavors and Mexican technique. What is this brilliant feat of fusion? Tortillas stuffed to the seams with cheese, curried sweet potatoes, and tender chickpeas, baked to crispy perfection. Drizzle these eat-with-one-hand wonders with dollops of yogurt for a tart punch, and top with lightly charred corn salsa for extra pops of color.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/654a656e33e8a37769159981-9a317769.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/654a656e33e8a37769159981.pdf
time required: 40 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/curried-sweet-potato-dosa-dillas-654a656e33e8a37769159981
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
cuisine: Southeast Asia
nutrition:
  calories: 1050 kcal
  fat: 44 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 123 g
  sugar: 32 g
  protein: 30 g
  fiber: 14 g
  sodium: 1660 mg
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @sweet potato{6%ounce} into ½-inch pieces.

Toss sweet potato on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice @scallions{4}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}. Dice @tomatoes{2} into ¼-inch pieces. Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%400g can}; pat dry with paper towels. Drain @corn kernels{1}; pat dry with paper towels.

Once sweet potato has roasted for 15 minutes, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add garlic, @curry powder{1%tablespoon}, and half the tomatoes. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Add chickpeas, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, 1⁄3 cup @water{1/3%cup}, @butter{1%tablespoon}, and @sugar{1/2%teaspoon}. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, use 2⁄3 cup water, 2 TBSP butter, and 1 tsp sugar.

Turn off heat; add roasted sweet potato to pan and stir to combine. (Reserve baking sheet.) Taste and season with salt and pepper. Transfer filling to a large #bowl{}. Wash out pan.

Coat baking sheet used for sweet potato with @nonstick cooking spray{}. Arrange @flour tortillas{6} on prepared sheet in a single layer (divide between two prepared sheets for 4). Evenly divide chickpea filling between one side of each tortilla; top with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}.

Fold tortillas in half to create dosa-dillas; press down gently with a #spatula{} to flatten slightly.

Dividing evenly, brush tops of dosa-dillas with a drizzle of olive oil. Bake on top rack (top and middle racks for 4) until golden, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for filling over medium-high heat. Add corn and cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly charred, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, it might take a little longer to char. If corn begins to pop, cover pan.

Transfer charred corn to second large bowl. Add scallion greens, remaining tomatoes, and a large drizzle of @olive oil{}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide dosa-dillas between plates. Top with as much charred corn salsa and @yogurt{4%tablespoon} as you like. Serve.